 eine Gesellschaft mit vielen Widersprüchen, die Ordnung und Fortschritt auf ihre Staatsflagge geschrieben hat.  aBrazil: 500 years of complex and enthralling cultural history. Soccer, Copacabana, Carnival, Favelas, the Amazon-what is behind the prevailing images? Brazil's history spans far more-from the Portugese colonial rule to the aspiring Great Power. The volume provides for the first time a comprehensive cultural history of this diverse country, which has layed claim to a special status for 200 years. It challenges official explanations and offers unadorned views of Brazil. These depict a society containing many contradictions, one that wrote 'Order' and 'Progress' on its national flag.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aGeschichte. 4aGeschichtswissenschaft. 4aKolonialgeschichte. 4aKultur. 4aKulturgeschichte. 4aLateinamerika. 4aLiteratur. 4aPostkolonialismus. 4aSüdamerikanische Geschichte. 7aHISTORY / Latin America / South America.2bisacsh  aCultural History.  aHistory of Colonialism.  aHistory.  aLatin America.  aLiterature.  aPostcolonialism.  aSouth American History.1 aRodrigues-Moura, Enrique, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Complete Package 2010-2013z9783110352856oZDB-23-TSO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Geschichte 2010-2013z978311037073708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript: Complete eBook-Package 2013z9783110401219oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/transcript.9783839423912zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839423912423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839423912/original  a978-3-11-037073-7  transcript Highlight Col